# Boot Sequence

At the start of every non-trivial conversation, silently perform these steps.
Do not narrate them unless a problem is found.

## 1. Load Accumulated Knowledge

Read these files and hold their contents as background context:

- `/Users/abhinav.sinha/.cursor/skills/forever-learner/learnings.md` — apply
  all entries as additional constraints alongside existing skills and rules.
  Later entries supersede earlier ones on the same topic.
- `/Users/abhinav.sinha/.cursor/skills/known-issues-library/known-issues.md` —
  use for symptom matching when the user reports any error or data issue.
  Check the Quick Index first.

## 2. Check System Health

Read the **last 30 lines** of
`/Users/abhinav.sinha/.cursor/skills/forever-learner/evolution-changelog.md`.

- If any line contains `[ACTION REQUIRED]`, surface it to the user at the
  start of the conversation:
  "System health check flagged: [the message]. Want me to address it?"
- If the file doesn't exist, skip silently.

## 3–4. Harvest and weekly proposals (same pass)

If `/Users/abhinav.sinha/.cursor/scripts/harvest-output.md` is non-empty: offer to review candidates; on approval, append confirmed entries to `learnings.md` or `known-issues.md`, discard rejects, then clear the file.

If `/Users/abhinav.sinha/.cursor/scripts/weekly-proposals.md` is non-empty: summarize its first line, offer to walk through (promotions, consolidations, stale learnings, archivable KIs, pending harvests); apply promotions only after confirmation; then clear the file.

## 5. Priority Order

If multiple things need attention, address them in this order:
1. `[ACTION REQUIRED]` health alerts (system may be broken)
2. Weekly evolution proposals (system evolution cycle)
3. Harvest candidates (knowledge waiting for approval)
4. Normal conversation

## 6. Skip Conditions

Skip the full boot sequence for:
- One-line questions ("what time is it", "how do I X")
- Follow-up messages in an existing conversation (already loaded)
- Explicit user request to skip ("skip boot", "no preamble")
